<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="643" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d643">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 165.102/311</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in. Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW2" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <dateline>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-24">
                                <hi rend="italic">December 24, 1914</hi>.</date>
                            <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 2:45 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                        <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                        <p>Berlin’s 1171, 22d. Am informed further half-month dyestuff supply has
                            been released amounting to about 1,100 tons for shipment on <hi rend="italic">Berwind</hi>.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_GJW2">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>